### What are Mixins?

Mixins are a way to reuse code across multiple class hierarchies. A mixin can have fields and methods that are added to a class.

```dart
mixin Flyable {
  void fly() => print('Flying');
}

mixin Swimmable {
  void swim() => print('Swimming');
}

class Duck with Flyable, Swimmable {}

void main() {
  var duck = Duck();
  duck.fly();   // Flying
  duck.swim();  // Swimming
}
```

### Defining Mixins

```dart
mixin LoggerMixin {
  void log(String message) {
    print('[LOG]: $message');
  }

  void logError(String message) {
    print('[ERROR]: $message');
  }
}

class Service with LoggerMixin {
  void doSomething() {
    log('Starting operation');
    // ...
    log('Operation complete');
  }
}
```

### Mixin with on Clause

The `on` keyword restricts which classes can use the mixin.

```dart
class Animal {}

mixin Walker on Animal {
  void walk() => print('$runtimeType is walking');
}

class Dog extends Animal with Walker {}
// class Table with Walker {} // ERROR: Table does not extend Animal
```

### Mixin Composition

```dart
mixin TimestampMixin {
  DateTime get createdAt => DateTime.now();
}

mixin ValidationMixin {
  bool isEmpty(String value) => value.isEmpty;
  bool isValidEmail(String email) => email.contains('@');
}

class User with TimestampMixin, ValidationMixin {
  String name;
  User(this.name);
}
```

### Mixin vs Inheritance

| Aspect | extends | mixin (with) |
|--------|---------|-------------|
| Relationship | IS-A | HAS-A or CAN-DO |
| Multiple | No | Yes (multiple mixins) |
| Constructor | Can have | Cannot have |
| super access | Yes | Yes (with on clause) |

> **Key Point:** Use `mixin` keyword to define reusable code blocks. Use `with` to apply mixins to a class. Mixins are more flexible than inheritance for sharing behavior across unrelated classes.

codeExample:
mixin JsonSerializableMixin {
  Map<String, dynamic> toJson();

  String toJsonString() {
    return toJson().toString();
  }
}

mixin PrintableMixin {
  void printDetails() {
    print('Instance of $runtimeType');
  }
}

class Person with JsonSerializableMixin, PrintableMixin {
  String name;
  int age;

  Person(this.name, this.age);

  @override
  Map<String, dynamic> toJson() => {'name': name, 'age': age};
}

void main() {
  var person = Person('Alice', 30);
  print(person.toJsonString());
  person.printDetails();
}
